# CLAUDE.md Template — Add Prismor Security to Your Project
#
# Copy this section into your project's CLAUDE.md file.
# Replace PRISMOR_PATH with the path to your local Prismor clone.
#
# Quick setup:
#   git clone https://github.com/PrismorSec/prismor.git ~/.prismor
#   Then add the block below to your project's CLAUDE.md
#
# Or use the automated setup:
#   bash ~/.prismor/scripts/init.sh /path/to/your/project

## Security (Prismor)

At the start of every session, read `PRISMOR_PATH/skills/security.md` and follow its instructions.

This loads:
- Behavioral guardrails (deny-listed commands, secret protection, anti-prompt-injection)
- Live threat intelligence feed (daily-updated, signed CVE data for AI frameworks)
- Secure coding rules (OWASP Top 10 with multi-language code examples)
- LLM security rules (OWASP Top 10 for LLMs 2025)

For runtime protection, install Warden hooks:
```
python3 PRISMOR_PATH/warden/cli.py install-hooks --agent claude --workspace . --mode observe
```
